.RE
.B
\fBasync_get2(UserId, TargetName, Oids, SendOpts) ->\fR
\fB                    {ok, ReqId} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        UserId :: user_id(),\fR
\fB                        TargetName :: target_name(),\fR
\fB                        Oids :: [snmp:oid()],\fR
\fB                        SendOpts :: [SendOpt],\fR
\fB                        SendOpt ::\fR
\fB                            {context, snmp:context_name()} |\fR
\fB                            {timeout, pos_integer()} |\fR
\fB                            {community, snmp:community()} |\fR
\fB                            {sec_model, snmp:sec_model()} |\fR
\fB                            {sec_name, snmp:sec_name()} |\fR
\fB                            {sec_level, snmp:sec_level()} |\fR
\fB                            {max_message_size, snmp:mms()} |\fR
\fB                            {extra, term()},\fR
\fB                        ReqId :: request_id(),\fR
\fB                        Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Asynchronous \fIget-request\fR.

.PP
The reply, if it arrives, will be delivered to the user through a call to the \fIsnmpm_user\fR callback function \fIhandle_pdu\fR.

.PP
The send option \fItimeout\fR specifies for how long the request is valid (after which the manager is free to delete it).

.PP
The send option \fIextra\fR specifies an opaque data structure passed on to the net-if process. The net-if process included in this application makes, with one exception, no use of this info, so the only use for it (when using the built in net-if) would be tracing. The one usage exception is: \fIAny\fR tuple with \fIsnmpm_extra_info_tag\fR as its first element is reserved for internal use.

.PP
Some of the send options (\fIcommunity\fR, \fIsec_model\fR, \fIsec_name\fR, \fIsec_level\fR and \fImax_message_size\fR) are \fIoverride options\fR. That is, for \fIthis\fR request, they override any configuration done when the agent was registered.


.RE
.B
\fBasync_get_bulk2(UserId, TargetName, NonRep, MaxRep, Oids,\fR
\fB                      SendOpts) ->\fR
\fB                         {ok, ReqId} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             UserId :: user_id(),\fR
\fB                             TargetName :: target_name(),\fR
\fB                             NonRep :: non_neg_integer(),\fR
\fB                             MaxRep :: non_neg_integer(),\fR
\fB                             Oids :: [snmp:oid()],\fR
\fB                             SendOpts :: [SendOpt],\fR
\fB                             SendOpt ::\fR
\fB                                 {context, snmp:context_name()} |\fR
\fB                                 {timeout, pos_integer()} |\fR
\fB                                 {community, snmp:community()} |\fR
\fB                                 {sec_model, snmp:sec_model()} |\fR
\fB                                 {sec_name, snmp:sec_name()} |\fR
\fB                                 {sec_level, snmp:sec_level()} |\fR
\fB                                 {max_message_size, snmp:mms()} |\fR
\fB                                 {extra, term()},\fR
\fB                             ReqId :: request_id(),\fR
\fB                             Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Asynchronous \fIget-bulk-request\fR (See RFC1905).

.PP
The reply, if it arrives, will be delivered to the user through a call to the \fIsnmpm_user\fR callback function \fIhandle_pdu\fR.

.PP
The send option \fItimeout\fR specifies for how long the request is valid (after which the manager is free to delete it).

.PP
The send option \fIextra\fR specifies an opaque data structure passed on to the \fInet-if\fR process. The \fInet-if\fR process included in this application makes no use of this info, so the only use for it in such a configuration (when using the built in \fInet-if\fR) would be tracing.

.PP
Some of the send options (\fIcommunity\fR, \fIsec_model\fR, \fIsec_name\fR, \fIsec_level\fR and \fImax_message_size\fR) are \fIoverride options\fR. That is, for \fIthis\fR request, they override any configuration done when the agent was registered.


.RE
.B
