.RE
.B
\fBsync_get2(UserId, TargetName, Oids, SendOpts) ->\fR
\fB                   {ok, SnmpReply, Remaining} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                   when\fR
\fB                       UserId :: user_id(),\fR
\fB                       TargetName :: target_name(),\fR
\fB                       Oids :: [snmp:oid()],\fR
\fB                       SendOpts :: [SendOpt],\fR
\fB                       SendOpt ::\fR
\fB                           {context, snmp:context_name()} |\fR
\fB                           {timeout, pos_integer()} |\fR
\fB                           {community, snmp:community()} |\fR
\fB                           {sec_model, snmp:sec_model()} |\fR
\fB                           {sec_name, snmp:sec_name()} |\fR
\fB                           {sec_level, snmp:sec_level()} |\fR
\fB                           {max_message_size, snmp:mms()} |\fR
\fB                           {extra, term()},\fR
\fB                       SnmpReply :: snmp_reply(),\fR
\fB                       Remaining :: non_neg_integer(),\fR
\fB                       Reason ::\fR
\fB                           {send_failed, ReqId, ActualReason} |\fR
\fB                           {invalid_sec_info, SecInfo, SnmpInfo} |\fR
\fB                           term(),\fR
\fB                       ReqId :: request_id(),\fR
\fB                       ActualReason :: term(),\fR
\fB                       SecInfo :: {SecTag, ExpectedValue, ReceivedValue},\fR
\fB                       SecTag :: atom(),\fR
\fB                       ExpectedValue :: term(),\fR
\fB                       ReceivedValue :: term(),\fR
\fB                       SnmpInfo :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Synchronous \fIget-request\fR.

.PP
\fIRemaining\fR is the remaining time of the given (or default) timeout time.

.PP
When \fIReason\fR is \fI{send_failed, ...}\fR it means that the \fInet-if\fR process failed to send the (\fIget-request\fR ) message. This could happen because of any number of reasons, i.e. encoding error. \fIActualReason\fR is the actual reason in this case.

.PP
The send option \fIextra\fR specifies an opaque data structure passed on to the \fInet-if\fR process. The \fInet-if\fR process included in this application makes, with one exception, no use of this info, so the only use for it (when using the built in \fInet-if\fR) would be tracing. The one usage exception is: \fIAny\fR tuple with \fIsnmpm_extra_info_tag\fR as its first element is reserved for internal use.

.PP
Some of the send options (\fIcommunity\fR, \fIsec_model\fR, \fIsec_name\fR, \fIsec_level\fR and \fImax_message_size\fR) are \fIoverride options\fR. That is, for \fIthis\fR request, they override any configuration done when the agent was registered.

.PP
For \fISnmpInfo\fR, see the user callback function handle_report.


